gomodel:SYNGO_5164  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Overexpression of FAAH in hippocampal glutamatergic neurons leads to increased degradation of anandamide (AEA) and palmitoylethanolamide (PEA).\n\nFigure 3: Elevated FAAH levels in hippocampal pyramidal neurons increase LTP, but not eLTD, iLTD, DSE, or DSI in hippocampal CA1 pyramidal cells.\n\n\"This approach led to specific FAAH overexpression at the postsynaptic site of CA1-CA3 neurons, to increased FAAH enzymatic activity, and, in consequence, to decreased hippocampal levels of AEA and palmitoylethanolamide (PEA), but the levels of the second major endocannabinoid 2-arachidonoyl glycerol (2-AG) and of oleoylethanolamide (OEA) were unchanged.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Male mice (2-3 months old) were housed in temperature-controlled and humidity-controlled rooms with a 12-h light-dark cycle and food provided ad libitum.\"\n\nEndocannabinoid extraction and liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry:\n\nLipid extractions and determination of AEA, PEA, OEA, 2-AG, and AA concentrations were performed as previously described [24]. PMID:36152174" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5164" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

